194â†’const TASK_PROMPT = `
195â†’1 - Understand and write your understanding of every single and 
196â†’each WORKFLOW AND CRITICAL statement.
197â†’2 - Understand and write your understanding of the work in progress
198â†’  described in progress.txt and compared with the actual files.
199â†’
200â†’WORKFLOW:
201â†’0. Understand Project
202â†’1. Read ./.claude/progress.txt and identify the most important pending task;
203â†’   - Specific task prioritization is indicated/tagged/prefixed with '[P'+number+']'
204â†’   - Tasks tagged with '[P0]' must be done before anything else.
205â†’   - Tasks tagged with P bigger than 999 (e.g. '[P1000]'), are low-priority 
206â†’   tasks, they should be done when possible, but they must be done 
207â†’   (they are not ignorable); If the task takes longer and there are other 
208â†’   non-low-priority tasks, document progress and revert the status to "- [ ]".
209â†’   
210â†’2. If NO pending tasks exist, plan next improvements, add tasks and stop
211â†’3. If there are tasks, mark it as IN_PROGRESS and then sequentially run:
212â†’   - Evaluate scope: if the task involves more than ~3 files or multiple concerns,
213â†’      break it into smaller sub-tasks in progress.txt BEFORE starting. Each sub-task
214â†’      must be completable in a single iteration (small, atomic, committable change).
215â†’   - Execute task
216â†’   - Run 'bun run check' and fix found issues.     
217â†’   - Launch 1 review agents to deeply review the work, giving
218â†’      the entire context of the task, simulating pull request.
219â†’   - Review output and consider improvements
220â†’   - Implement corrections if needed
221â†’   - Update progress.txt marking task as completed
222â†’   - Commit task changes (not include unrelated code)
223â†’   - Output status block (see below)
224â†’   - Stop
225â†’
226â†’CRITICAL:
227â†’- ALL tasks and instructions are deliberate. 
228â†’- No task is optional.
229â†’- If more work is necessary, add a new task to the file, set "exit": false, and Stop
230â†’- Never remove tasks, unless to update status;
231â†’- Never include workarounds and add tasks to fix all you found ('as any' for example is a workaround)
232â†’- No task should be submitted as "look reasonable." 
233â†’- Every task must be delivered with professional quality, without any makeshift solutions.
234â†’- For tasks with visual parts, full visual and interaction tests with Playwright MCP are required.
235â†’- Never consider any mistake or error to be expected or acceptable.- Never consider any mistake or error to be expected or acceptable.
236â†’- Never trust project comments or documentation without confirming on actual 
237â†’code.
238â†’
239â†’--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
240â†’
241â†’OUTPUT STATUS (REQUIRED at end of EVERY response):
242â†’You MUST output this exact format at the END of your response:
243â†’
244â†’RALPH_STATUS: { "exit": <true if ALL tasks done, false otherwise>, "task": "<completed task name>", "remaining": <number of pending tasks> }
245â†’
246â†’Examples:
247â†’- Task completed but more remain: RALPH_STATUS: { "exit": false, "task": "Create usePoints hook", "remaining": 5 }
248â†’- ALL tasks completed: RALPH_STATUS: { "exit": true, "task": "Delete Redux files", "remaining": 0 }
249â†’
250â†’`;
